    <section class="app-c-banner app-c-banner--grid" aria-label="Notice">
      <h2 class="app-c-banner__title">Summary</h2>
  <p class="app-c-banner__desc">
          Responses are invited to the review of sections 34-37 of the Scotland Act 2012 by 9th April 2018.
        <br></br><br></br>
        <strong>This consultation was held on <a href="http://www.scotland-judiciary.org.uk/25/1888/%e2%80%98Compatibility-issues%e2%80%99-consultation">another website</a>.</strong>

  </p>

    <p class="app-c-banner__desc">        This consultation ran from<br></br><span class="consultation-date"><time datetime="2018-02-02T00:00:00.000+00:00">2 February 2018</time> to
        <time datetime="2018-04-09T00:00:00.000+01:00">11:59pm on 8 April 2018</time></span>
</p>
</section>




    <div class="consultation-description">
      <h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--mobile-top-margin  ">Consultation description</h2>

      
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>The Secretary of State for Scotland has invited the Lord Justice General to chair a review of sections 34-37 of the Scotland Act 2012. The review group established by the Lord Justice General has published a consultation paper. Responses are invited by  9th April 2018.</p>

<p>(You may need to open the link twice for the consultation page to open)</p>
</div>
</div>


